<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="arrange-v">arrange <strong><em>v</em></strong> ★</h1>
<p>英 /ə'reɪndʒ/    美 /ə'reɪndʒ/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>安排；筹划</strong></h4>
<p>to make plans and preparations for sth to happen：</p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>In China, many parents arrange everything for their children and pave the way for their success.
在中国， 许多父母为孩子安排一切，为他们的成功铺路。</p><footer>2013 福建书面表达改</footer></div>

<ul>
<li>arrange (for sb / sth) to do sth:</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Dave arranged for someone to drive him home. 
戴夫安排人开车送他回家。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Nobel arranged in his will to give the largest part of his money to establish the Nobel prizes. 
诺贝尔在遗嘱中把他的大部分钱捐献出来设立诺贝尔奖。</p><footer>2009 广东</footer></div>

<ul>
<li>arrange (sth) with sb (about sth):</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I’ve arranged with the neighbours about feeding the cat while we are away. 
我们外出期间喂猫的事，我已和邻居安排妥了。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The headmaster arranged a meeting with all of the teachers. 
校长安排了和所有老师开会。</p></div>

<ul>
<li>arrange + wh- to do sth:</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>We haven't yet arranged when to meet.
我们还没定好何时见面。</p></div>

<ul>
<li>arrange + that 从句：</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The manager arranged that the meeting should be put off for a couple of days.
经理安排会议推迟几天。</p></div>

<h4 id="2">2.★ <strong>排列；整理</strong></h4>
<p>to put sth in a particular order：</p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The list is arranged alphabetically. 
这个名单是按字母顺序排列的。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>You can arrange things from beginning to end, small to large or by some other order.
你可以按照从头到尾、从小到大或别的顺序来整理物品。</p><footer>2012 陕西</footer></div>

<h4 id="3">3.<strong>编写 / 改编 (乐曲)</strong></h4>
<p>to write or change a piece of music：</p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>write and arrange musical compositions 
编写并改编音乐作品</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">固定搭配</h2>
<h3 id="arranged-marriage">arranged marriage</h3>
<p>1.<strong>包办婚姻</strong>  </p></div>